-- Asia Private Equity Weekly News, January 20, 2014
-- 
-- Sun Jan 19, 2014 08:00PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 20 (Reuters) - News and developments in Asia private equity from Reuters News for the week ending Jan. 17.

JANUARY 17 EXCLUSIVE-ANHEUSER-Busch InBev SA <ABI.BR> is in advanced discussions to buy South Korea's Oriental Brewery from private equity owners KKR & Co LP <KKR.N> and Affinity Equity Partners for more than $4.5 billion, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0KR0W] CHINA-FOCUSED private equity firm Boyu Capital, whose partners include former TPG Capital [TPG.UL] executive Mary Ma and the grandson of former Chinese president Jiang Zemin, has raised $1.5 billion for its second buyout fund, according to people with knowledge of the matter. [ID:nL3N0KR1RB]  CARLYLE GROUP <CG.O> is seeking to raise up to $290 million by selling a stake in Chinese home appliance maker Haier Electronics Group Ltd <1169.HK>, IFR reported, citing a term sheet of the deal. [ID:nL3N0KR3Q3]  CHINA DIAPER maker AAB Group, backed by Asia private equity firm RRJ Capital, is seeking to raise up to $300 million in a Hong Kong stock market listing, IFR reported. [ID:nL3N0KR44U] CITIC CAPITAL Holdings Ltd, which is backed by CITIC Group Corp [CITIC.UL] and China sovereign wealth fund CIC [CIC.UL] said it has established a multi-strategy hedge fund, CCTrack Solutions. [ID:nL3N0KR2C5]  SINGAPORE'S GIC Pte Ltd [GIC.UL] is partnering a group of investors to buy $1.3 billion worth of Manhattan office space from Time Warner Inc <TWX.N>, as the sovereign wealth fund steps up its purchases of real estate where it sees increasing value. [ID:nL2N0KQ1QR]  U.S. PRIVATE equity firm Cerberus Capital Management LP [CBS.UL] has decided to sell its entire majority stake in Japanese property operator Kokusai Kogyo Co to its founding family for 130-140 billion yen ($1.25-1.34 billion), people with direct knowledge of the deal said. [ID:nT9N0KG01X]   JANUARY 16 CITIC CAPITAL Holdings said it has completed the privatisation of AsiaInfo-Linkage Inc <ASIA.O>, together with consortium members which included CITIC Private Equity, in a deal valued at around $900 million. The deal is China's second-largest private equity backed privatisation and CITIC Capital's sixth take-private deal. (http://link.reuters.com/wyj26v) JANUARY 15 SEIBU HOLDINGS Inc applied to relist its shares on the Tokyo bourse, as the company starts negotiations with top shareholder Cerberus over a proposed sale of much of the U.S. fund's stake, sources said. [ID:nL3N0KP2PX]  STATE INVESTOR 1Malaysia Development Bhd has invited investment banks to pitch for advisory roles for an up to $2 billion IPO of its power assets, the country's biggest listing in nearly two years, sources said. [ID:nL3N0KP2NS]   JANUARY 14 ROSE ROCK Group, an investment management firm backed by the Rockefeller family, has agreed to help develop a $2.5 billion resort project in Vietnam. [ID:nL3N0KO2CR]   JANUARY 13